import {
  Button,
  CardContent,
  Container,
  FormControl,
  FormControlLabel,
  Grid,
  InputLabel,
  makeStyles,
  TextField,
  Typography,
} from "@material-ui/core"
import { red } from "@material-ui/core/colors"

const useStyles = makeStyles((theme) => ({
  form: {
    width: "100%",
    margin: theme.spacing(2),
  },
  container: {
    marginTop: theme.spacing(8),
  },
}))

const Login = () => {
  const classes = useStyles()
  return (
    <Container className={classes.container} maxWidth="xs">
      <Typography component={"h1"}>Sign in</Typography>
      <form>
        <Grid container spacing={3}>
          <Grid item xs={12}>
            <Grid container spacing={2}>
              <Grid item xs={12}>
                <TextField
                  fullWidth
                  label="Email"
                  name="email"
                  size="small"
                  variant="outlined"
                />
              </Grid>
              <Grid item xs={12}>
                <TextField
                  fullWidth
                  label="Password"
                  name="password"
                  size="small"
                  type="password"
                  variant="outlined"
                />
              </Grid>
            </Grid>
          </Grid>
          <Grid item xs={12}>
            <Button color="primary" fullWidth type="submit" variant="contained">
              Log in
            </Button>
          </Grid>
        </Grid>
      </form>
    </Container>
  )
}

export default Login
